  "body": "### User Story\n\nAs a user/developer, I'd like to run Status Desktop as a bootnode so that I can share it with my friends who can't access Status cluster,\n\n### Description\n\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Feature\n\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\n*Summary*: When I go to Profile tab, I should be able to set an option to run Status Desktop as a bootnode. When I share my enode address (possible when https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/6133 is done), other Status apps should be able to use my instance as a bootnode.\n\n### Solution\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\n*Summary*: \n- add an option to turn Status Desktop into bootnode,\n- Status Desktop should operate normally just like without the option turned on.\n\n### Additional Information\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n* Status version: v0.0.1 (`0caab1f7c`)\n* Operating System: Desktop",
